Russian Equity Movers: Gazprom Neft and TNK-BP Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-05-16T16:02:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/russian-equity-movers-gazprom-neft-and-tnk-bp-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 0.6
percent to 1,622.98 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, paring an
earlier loss of as much as 1.7 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index dropped 1.1 percent to 1,846.32.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX), Russia’s second-biggest
producer, declined to its lowest close since Nov. 3, sliding 1.6
percent to 121.6 rubles. Crude fell 80 cents to $98.85 a barrel
in  New York .  TNK-BP (TNBP RX) surged the most in more than a month,
adding 3.4 percent to 82.69 rubles as BP Plc seeks to agree on a
buyout of its billionaire partners in  Russia ’s third-largest oil
producer, according to people with knowledge of the talks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
